<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="367" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,798,1410]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1236,1261]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[645,791,1236,1260]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrosteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striifrons">
<emphasis box="[645,791,1236,1260]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="367">M. striifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the characters of the aedeagus, but can be differentiated from the latter by the aedeagal shaft having a pair of protuberances dorsally subapically, 
<number box="[1406,1420,1275,1299]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367" value="2.0">2</number>
nd acrotergite with trunk horizontal and 
<number box="[568,582,1314,1338]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367" value="2.0">2</number>
nd tergal apodeme not extending beyond tergite posteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="367" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,798,1410]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1349,1374]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName box="[582,671,1350,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrosteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brochus">
<emphasis box="[582,671,1350,1374]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="367">brochus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the pair of prominent teeth on the dorsum of the aedeagal shaft subapically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
